OL,3,CChildren often having say in home move
OL,4,Cchoices ` survey
OL,6,FThree-quarters (74%) of families say
OL,7,Ftheir children have a say over final
OL,8,Fhousing choices during the home moving
OL,9,Fprocess, a survey has found.
OL,11,FMen (32%) are more likely than women
OL,12,F(25%) to take the lead on the home
OL,13,Fmoving process itself, according to
OL,14,Fthe research, commissioned by Zoopla.
OL,16,FMale movers are more likely to take
OL,17,Fthe lead in setting a budget (33%
OL,18,Fversus 19%), deciding on the mortgage
OL,19,F(34% versus 17%) and arranging
OL,20,Fconveyancing (38% versus 24%) than
OL,21,Fwomen, the survey indicated.
